  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Cut the<strong> potatoes</strong> (skins on) into small bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 15-20 min or until fork-tender</p><p>Once cooked, drain and return to the pot to steam dry</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1614006134039-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1614006134039-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1614006134039-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1614006134039-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1614006134039-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut the <strong>aubergine<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into quarters lengthways</p><p>Score the flesh in a criss-cross pattern, taking care to not cut the skin</p><p>Add the <strong>scored</strong> <strong>aubergine quarters </strong>to a baking tray, cut-side up</p><p>Drizzle with <strong>olive oil</strong>, sprinkle over the<strong> smoked</strong> <strong>paprika</strong> and season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, then put the tray in the oven for 25-30 min or until softened – this is your <strong>paprika aubergine</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1614006142629-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1614006142629-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1614006142629-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1614006142629-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1614006142629-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the aubergine is cooking, strip the <strong>mint</strong> <strong>leaves</strong> from their stems and chop them roughly, discard the stems</p><p>Grate the <strong>cucumber<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Squeeze any excess water out of the <strong>grated cucumber</strong></p><p>Combine the <strong>grated cucumber</strong>, <strong>chopped mint</strong> and <strong>half</strong> the <strong>cultured coconut </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) in a bowl with a small pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>– this is your <strong>coconut raita</strong></p>",
